        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 6:59PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 659 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Kingston to 8 miles west of Sandusky to 6
miles east of Marlette. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sandusky, Cass City, Marlette, Mayville, Deckerville, Port Sanilac,
Forestville, Argyle, Carsonville, Kingston, Applegate, Watertown,
Elmer, Forester, Wilmot, Minden, Juhl, New Greenleaf, Deford, and
Richmondville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
